c8 x1c he y160b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 Corinthians 14:20 (translated &quot;men&quot;) ; </div><div class="t mea4 x5a he yee9 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eph. 4:13, 14; Heb. 5:13, 14 (translated &quot;of </div><div class="t m2ae x5a he ydcf ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">full age&quot;). The verb form means &quot;to fin-</div><div class="t ma32 x1c he ydbf ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ish,&quot; &quot;to complete,&quot; &quot;to perfect.&quot; </div><div class="t m558 x7 h5 ybbf ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m318 x9f h5 yda0 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lay Aside Every Weight. </div><div class="t m628 x165 he yda0 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The pic-</div><div class="t mab x1c he yeeb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ture is of an overweight athlete stripping </div><div class="t m642 x1c he yd4a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">off excess fat that would be a handicap to </div><div class="t m430 x1c he yd2f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him in a forthcoming athletic contest. The </div><div class="t mb44 x1c he yd17 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Greeks used the expression in this sense, and </div><div class="t m7ef x1c he yd69 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">since Hebrews 12:1, 2 pictures the Christian </div><div class="t m2269 x33 h35 y8c8 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">134 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
